A man was shot dead at a tavern in Mamelodi, Tshwane, in the early hours of Monday. Police spokesperson Col Dimakatso Sello said three suspects wearing balaclavas and armed with pistols arrived at the Monaco tavern and found  a group of people sitting around. “The trio fired in the air before approaching the 33-year-old man and shooting him twice,” Sello said. She said the motive was unknown and  police were investigating a case of murder. TimesLIVE